325
00:22:19,670 --> 00:22:23,380
However in 2012, the global price of
carbon

326
00:22:23,380 --> 00:22:27,570
credits crashed and hasn't recovered to
its earlier highs.

327
00:22:27,570 --> 00:22:32,270
So it's not clear if this strategy will,
will be productive in the future.

328
00:22:34,620 --> 00:22:38,660
The largest example of carbon credit
financing in HWTS

329
00:22:38,660 --> 00:22:42,610
is that of Vestergaard Frandsen's Carbon
for Water project,

330
00:22:42,610 --> 00:22:46,200
in which nearly a million Lifestraw family
filters were

331
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:50,890
distributed for free throughout western
Kenya, in entire communities.

